# macOS — Homebrew & Cursor Agent setup

Use this when the user needs **Homebrew**, **`brew`-based tools**, or the **Cursor Agent CLI** on **macOS**.

## Homebrew — install

- **Official installer** (interactive; needs **sudo** + TTY — run in the user’s Terminal, not the agent-only shell):

```bash
/bin/bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)"
```

- **This repo** also installs Homebrew if missing: `scripts/setup-cursor-agent.sh` (same sudo/Tty requirement).

## Homebrew — PATH in `~/.zshrc`

After install, the installer prints two `eval "$(...brew shellenv)"` lines. Ensure **one** of them is in `~/.zshrc` so new terminals see `brew`:

| Mac              | Add to `~/.zshrc` |
|------------------|-------------------|
| **Apple Silicon** | `eval "$(/opt/homebrew/bin/brew shellenv)"` |
| **Intel**        | `eval "$(/usr/local/bin/brew shellenv)"` |

Then: `source ~/.zshrc` or open a new terminal.

## Homebrew — verify

```bash
which brew
brew --version
brew doctor
```

If `which brew` is empty, PATH is not set for that shell — fix `~/.zshrc` as above.

## Homebrew — maintain

```bash
brew update
brew upgrade   # optional; upgrades installed formulae
```

## Project script location

- `scripts/setup-cursor-agent.sh` — installs Homebrew (if needed), then **git**, **gh**, **node**, **Cursor CLI**, and adds **`~/.local/bin`** to PATH.

## How to run the project script (human, interactive Terminal)

```bash
bash "/path/to/Cursor Hackathon March/scripts/setup-cursor-agent.sh"
```

Or copy the script to **Desktop** and run: `cd ~/Desktop && bash setup-cursor-agent.sh`

Then: `source ~/.zshrc`, then **`agent`**.

## If the user has no admin password

Homebrew’s default install **requires sudo**. Without it, do not assume `brew` works. They need password reset, another admin, or IT; offer non-Homebrew installs (e.g. **nodejs.org**) when appropriate.

## Agent terminal limitation

The AI/agent environment often **cannot** complete Homebrew install (no TTY / sudo). Direct the user to **Terminal** or **Cursor’s integrated terminal** on their Mac.
